Have you or your family ever wondered about the culture of another country? Are you a â€œteen-friendlyâ€ home? Would you like to share a â€œonce-in-a-lifetimeâ€ experience with someone that you could have a life-long connection to because of it? If so, consider hosting a high school international student for the 2019-2020 school year.

We have a 16-year old female student from Switzerland that is in need of a host family from mid-January through June 2020. A monthly stipend in the amount of $800 is available through a CSIET approved agency. If interested, contact Donna at 732-269-1100, ext. 3211 for help with the application.

Central Regional has no affiliation with any agency.

When Middle School student Emily heard that students in our community were in need of hygiene products, she wanted to help. With her mom and grandma, Emily raised enough funds to put together 25 bags of products to distribute to students in need. We posted about Emilyâ€™s fundraiser on our social media platforms where Tom from â€œJF Party Dragonâ€ took notice. â€œJF Party Dragonâ€ is a local charity organization doing amazing work around our community like food drives, toy drives, cards for veterans, and so much more. Today, Tom came to CR Middle School to surprise Emily with a very generous donation of 25 more hygiene bags! Emily was so surprised! Emilyâ€™s mom and grandma even made an appearance to show their support! Keep up the great work Emily and Thank You to â€œJF Party Dragonâ€ for supporting our community, school, and mostly our students.

Be sure to check out @JFPartyDragon on Instagram or visit their website https://jfpartydragon.com

PLEASE HELP SUPPORT CENTRAL REGIONAL

HOW YOU CAN SUPPORT OUR SCHOOLS

Donating:

You have the ability to select exactly where your generous donation will go. You are able to directly support high school or middle school academic programs, sports teams, clubs and projects within our school district such as the Football Team, Autism Awareness Club, English or Music Departments or a new sound system for the auditorium just to name a few! You can even set up a monthly donation plan, the option is yours!!

Sharing:

In addition to your generous donation, you can help by sharing this page by utilizing our "one touch" sharing buttons with your family, friends and community!

Upon donating, you will receive a tax deductible receipt in your email. Thank you for your support and Go Eagles!!!

Click the link below for more info!

Kindness in Chalk was started in 2014 by Minnesota blogger, Nicki Brunner. Brunner and her daughter were drawing with chalk outside their home. As neighbors walked by, they grinned at the smiley face and â€œHave a happy day!â€ message that adorned the sidewalk. That sparked an idea in Brunner: How could she translate these kinds of positive messages and positive reactions to her sonâ€™s school?

After getting permission from the principal, the Kindness in Chalk Day was a go. Brunner promoted the idea on her blog and on social media sites. The day was a hit locally and has since become an activity in communities nationwide. Simple yet meaningful!

Here are the fabulous creations from our Art students.

post_text:
Central Regional is happy to announce that we have added a 3rd romance language for the students to study. In addition to Spanish and French, we will now offer Italian in the HS World Language Department. Italian is a romance language spoken by over 60 million people around the world.

Speaking Italian gives you access to the world with native speakers from Rome to Milan to Sicily to San Marino. Italian is considered one of the easiest languages for a native English speaker to learn. The grammar and sentence structure are different from English, but simpler. Because both languages have Latin roots, they also share thousands of cognates â€“ words that sound the same and have the same meanings.

Any student interested in taking Italian next year or if you have any questions, please contact the Guidance Department at 732-269-1100 ext. 3208/3268.
